description:
This is a 29 minute workout called 'Yoga To Reduce Stress | 30 Min Slow Flow - Relaxing Stretches + Savasana' from the channel Jess Yoga.
The workout falls under Flexibility/Yoga and Flexibility/Stretching.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Zen Flow and The Reboot Workout vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: This gentle and relaxing full body yoga class will take you through mindful movement meant to support your physical + mental healthy by reducing stress. You will be encouraged to move with your breath while staying aware of your bodily sensations. This class is for all levels.

We begin with a gentle flow of child's pose to cobra with a side body and lower back stretch, locust pose to open the shoulders and a seated toe stretch. The sequence continues with downward dog, rag-doll, seated neck stretches, head to knee pose, seated wide legged forward fold, reclined twist and savasana.

I hope you enjoy the class! Let me know in the comments how it leaves you feeling. Be sure to download the Jess Yoga app for more exclusive practices. See you on the mat üòä
